		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Jun 28th 11:51 AM2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1088062913228941159&num=8&post=1&replyto=1088437890736259622"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1088437890736259622></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=250373"><span id=>harmonize</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />9 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=harmonize&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>If you have thunderous drums of Karana or better, you can just run around in the tightest circle you can. (Forward and left OR right together). the speed that the drum modifier gives you, keeps you just out of range of the mobs while staying in range for your song.<br>This can make you dizzy. Play around with camera angles to find one that gives you the best view while not making you sick.<br><br>A word of warning. IF you have any lag and one of the mobs 'jumps' towards you, there is the possiblity of getting stunned. Then you have ALL the mobs in the kite beating on you. That'll probably kill you. I'd suggest do no more than 6-8 (depending on how hard they hit) at once.<br>This doesn't work for giants and other mobs that have a larger 'hit' radius.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
