		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Obladi&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>By far the best way to AE kite is with Run Speed 3 AA... it should be a bard's first 3 AAs instead of regen, as it allows all sorts of fun to be had.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mobs in PoValor run nearly as fast as Selo's with Trueborn Drum of Dark Rites, bard at about 260+ and the mobs at 220+ (base run speed is 100 by the way)  and run speed 3 is about 130...  While still slower than the mobs in this zone, I have found it possible, with a decent radius to be able to AE kite the mobs here (minus the summoners.)  Start by running with selos and your drum, pulling all the mobs you can find.  Start running your circle, and allow selos to drop after you've got a good rhythm going... try it with a few mobs to start out with, it will be difficult to get a selos up again if you do get stunned or hit with more than one mob chasing you.<br><br>My favorite place to kite post 55 is Nadox... it will take you to 65 if you are patient, and the low Hitpoint to XP ratio makes up for the time it takes to get there.  At level 62, I still am getting at least .5% per kill, and the mobs have less than half the HP of planar mobs...<br><br>As for AA points... nothing's faster than Nadox... level 54+ mobs, a full AE kite of the Luggald room will get you a full blue per kite.  yeah... that's 5 ticks per kite or more.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Uber Bard of Vallon Zek<br>Master of AE kiting, Chant Kiting, and not getting hit by mobs</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></t